If you are a vinyl records lover or collector and enjoy good old-fashioned music, then Soir e Gardens on Kindaruma Road, Nairobi is the place for you to be every first Sunday of the month. The restaurant plays host to a group of DJs, music lovers and collectors all brought together for an evening of fun, food and lively conversations by their love for Vinyl records.Last Sunday, the group lit up Soir e taking customers back to the days of Anna Mwale, Manou Dibango, Johnny Cash and the like. In attendance included 'We Love Vinyl Worldwide' founding member Jack Ojiambo, saxophonist Jackson Munala, Oxfam International's Samah Hassoun and lawyer Wanda Atsiaya.